Title : Haakon Andreas Olsen
Text : '''Haakon Andreas Olsen''' (18 September 1923{{cn|date=December 2016}}&nbsp;– 22 August 2010) was a [[Norway|Norwegian]] physicist.

Olsen was born in [[Tromsø]] and [[examen artium|finished]] his secondary education in 1944. He enrolled at the [[Norwegian Institute of Technology]], first in architecture, then in technical physics and finally [[theoretical physics]] under [[Harald Wergeland]]. He graduated with the [[sivilingeniør|siv.ing.]] degree in 1950 and the [[dr.techn.]] degree in 1953. His specialty was [[elementary particle physics]].<ref name=obit/>

Olsen was appointed as a [[docent]] at the Norwegian Institute of Technology in 1956 and professor in 1962. In 1965 he became a professor at the [[Norwegian College of General Sciences|Norwegian College of Teaching in Trondheim]], where he served as rector from 1969 to 1975. He became a professor emeritus at the age of 70, but continued working at the university on a daily basis into his 80s.<ref name=obit/>

The Norwegian College of Teaching in Trondheim became a part of the [[University of Trondheim]], where Olsen chaired the interim board from 1972 to 1975. He was also central in the development of [[Dragvoll]] campus. He also chaired the [[CERN]] Committee within the science research council [[NTNF]] from 1980 to 1993,<ref name=obit/> having been a committee member since 1966. He also edited the Norwegian Physical Society's magazine ''Fra fysikkens verden''.<ref name=ntb/>

Olsen was a fellow of the [[Royal Norwegian Society of Sciences and Letters]] (praeses 1990 to 1995),<ref name=obit/> fellow of the [[Central European Academy of Science and Art]] from 1999,<ref name=ntb/> of the [[Norwegian Academy of Science and Letters]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dnva.no/c26848/artikkel/vis.html?tid=27625|title=Gruppe 2: Fysikkfag (herunder astronomi, fysikk og geofysikk)|publisher=[[Norwegian Academy of Science and Letters]]|language=Norwegian|accessdate=4 May 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110605094726/http://www.dnva.no/c26848/artikkel/vis.html?tid=27625|archivedate=5 June 2011}}</ref> and honorary member of the [[Norwegian Physical Society]] from 1992.<ref name=ntb2>{{cite news|title=Haakon Andreas Olsen 70 år 18. september|agency=Norwegian News Agency|date=15 August 1993|language=Norwegian}}</ref>

Olsen resided at [[Gløshaugen]], near the Institute of Technology.<ref name=ntb>{{cite news|title=Haakon Andreas Olsen 80 år 18. september|agency=Norwegian News Agency|date=29 August 2003|language=Norwegian}}</ref> He died in August 2010.<ref name=obit>{{cite journal|title=Haakon A. Olsen In Memorian|last=Johnsson|first=Anders|author2=Mork, Kjell |author3=Olaussen, Kåre|author4=Osland, Per |date=2010|journal=Fra Fysikkens Verden|volume=72|issue=4|page=97–98|language=Norwegian|url=http://www.norskfysikk.no/nfs/ffv_old/2010/FFV_2010-4.pdf}}</ref>




